{
  "texts": [
    "When data is organized into categories, locating and retrieving specific items or concepts is easier.",
    "Moreover, categorization aligns with human cognitive processes.",
    "Humans naturally tend to categorize information to make sense of the world, and structured categories can help streamline thinking and decision-making; they also help to reduce the cognitive load required to process information.",
    "Instead of dealing with individual items, focusing on the characteristics and relationships within categories is possible.",
    "It can support decision-making by comparing options within categories, which can be valuable in product management, marketing, and research."
  ]
}